<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Berastagi</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Highland market town at 1,300 m. Strawberry farms, passionfruit, marquisa juice. Sunday farmers' market is one of Sumatra's most colourful.]]></description><Point><coordinates>98.508300,3.193300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mount Sibayak</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Active 2,212 m volcano with a rare easy summit — 3 hr return hike to the steaming crater floor. Sulfuric vents, hot streams, can reach the highest viewpoint without technical climbing. Local guides recommended.]]></description><Point><coordinates>98.492800,3.154700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Sipiso-piso</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[120 m single-thread waterfall on the steep northern rim of the Toba crater. Long view across the lake to Samosir. The 670-step path to the base is steep — bring a torch back up if you stay for sunset.]]></description><Point><coordinates>98.533300,2.994400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Parapat</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Mainland ferry port for Samosir. Hourly boats to Tuktuk. Old colonial Dutch hill station vibe; mango and durian along the lakeshore.]]></description><Point><coordinates>98.927200,2.662200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Tomok</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Samosir Island ferry landing. Old Toba Batak tombs and the Sigale-gale puppet — a wooden figure traditionally animated to dance at funerals (now performed for tourists, but still striking).]]></description><Point><coordinates>98.837800,2.645300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Tuktuk</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Peninsula on the east side of Samosir — the village backpackers fall asleep in for a week. Lakeside guesthouses; warm bathing in the lake; Batak musicians on most evenings.]]></description><Point><coordinates>98.865000,2.669400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Pangururan / Mount Pusuk Buhit</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[West side of Samosir. Hot springs at the base of Mount Pusuk Buhit (1,981 m), the Batak holy mountain — origin of the Batak people in their cosmology. Crossing point to mainland via a small bridge to Sumatra.]]></description><Point><coordinates>98.710600,2.617200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
